==English==
===Etymology===
A reference to the [[w:Fifth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution|Fifth Amendment]] to the United States Constitution, which states, among other things, that one may not be required to [[testify]] against oneself.

===Verb===
'''[[take]] the [[fifth]]'''
#{{idiom}} To [[decline]] to [[comment]], especially on grounds that it might be [[incriminating]].
#:''If you ask me who ate the last of the ice cream, I will simply '''take the fifth'''.''